<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3066729>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Hetereleotris semisquamata sp. nov. PMR VP3053, holotype, female, 12.58 mm, caudal fin damaged, Red Sea, Southern Egypt, Shams Alam. A: alive specimen; B: freshly collected specimen; C: preserved specimen; D: stained preserved specimen, squamation visible. Photos by S.V. Bogorodsky (A & B), M. Kovačić (C & D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3066729/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3066731>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Hetereleotris semisquamata sp. nov. Cephalic sensory papillae: PMR VP3053, holotype, female, female, 12.58 mm, caudal fin damaged, Red Sea, Southern Egypt, Shams Alam. Terminology in text. Drawing by M. Kovačić." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3066731/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

